site.title: Laura Worboys

elements.innerHtml: I am a driven lifelong learner transitioning careers from Health into CS. Working under pressure, leading people, engaging with customers, and problem solving are some of the skills I developed in my Health career. CS has taught me to build full-stack applications in Java, Python, and JavaScript. Im passionate about CS because I relish being creative, conquering challenges as part of a team, and learning continuously. My skills and passion together make me a distinctive engineer who will provide a unique perspective on your team.
Java, Python, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Node.js, React.js, Express, MongoDB, Git, Unit Testing, Teamwork, Commincation, Self-Starter, Fast Learner

Q: How are you able to get an MSCS ?

A: Northeastern University has a program called Align that helps students transitioning careers have a years worth of intensive CS classes prior to moving onto the Master courses

Q: Why did you choose to transition careers ?

A: What interested me about both Medicine and Engineering is I wanted to know how the object or body worked, what made them tick, how to debug a health issue or coding question, and how to make them more efficient

Q: What areas are you interested in?

A: Im interested in backend positions, frontend positions, and full stack positions
